Evangeline Lilly (She is from Canada, btw) played Tauriel, a woodland elf and Legolas' lover.
Elven warrioress who lived in Mirkwood with King Thranduil and his son Legolas. Though she was not mentioned by name in The Hobbit book itself, the character was created for Peter Jackson's film adaptation. She had an important role in both Desolation of Smaug and Battle of Five Armies. In these films, her relationship with Legolas blossoms into romance, adding another dimension to their storylines. Her character became controversial because of the love triangle between Thorin Oakenshield, Legolas and Tauriel. For that reason alone, many fans consider her one of the most interesting characters in all six movies. Many also appreciate her fighting skills. While Galadriel and Arwen are skilled fighters too, they don't get as much screen time battling foes like Tauriel does. And although some may argue about whether or not Tolkien intended there to be so much attention paid to female characters, the fact remains that audiences loved them just as much--if not more than--their male counterparts. As we see in her moments onscreen with Bard the Breaker and Thranduil, she often steals every scene. Because of this strong presence on camera, it seems only natural that someone would want to cosplay as Tauriel someday.
